         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Chief Secretary's Office ¶ Melbourne 5th May 1871. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I have the honor by direction of the Chief Secretary to request that you will be good enough to inform Mr Ferguson of your Department tha...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.05.05a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 1512, p. 700, unit 25, VPRS 1187/P, outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 5th May 1871.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor by direction of the Chief Secretary to request that you will be good enough to inform Mr Ferguson of your Department that the papers in the matter of his being provided with quarters were referred to the Board of Inquiry on the Botanic Gardens who have not yet made any report.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Ferguson had requested that he be provided with a cottage in the Botanic Garden, and M had been instructed to serve notice on the gardener David Coller to vacate the one he had occupied. The cottage was aparently still occupied by Coller in December 1870 when in M to D. Coller, 29 December 1870,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M wrote passing on the Chief Secretary's inquiry about occupancy. There is a minute, probably by the Chief Secretary, with the letter: 'let this matter stand over till the Board on the Botanical Gardens sends in its report'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Director Botanic Gardens</p>
         </div>
      </body>
